OL,7,FConfidence fell in other key areas in
OL,8,Fthe six years between the survey. Just
OL,9,F33 per cent of people said in 2022
OL,10,Fthat the service's policies were
OL,11,Fapplied "fairly and consistently"
OL,12,F(down 38 points) and 52 per cent said
OL,13,Fthey felt able to "speak up and
OL,14,Fexpress my honest opinion about my
OL,15,Frole" (down 16 points).
OL,17,FAfter the 2018 report, the service
OL,18,Ftold employees it would run follow-up
OL,19,Fsurveys every two years to monitor
OL,20,F"action plans" aimed at tackling
OL,21,Fproblems raised by staff.
