OL,7,F"Firefighters do lifesaving work and
OL,8,Fthey must be able to work without fear
OL,9,Fof bullying, harassment or
OL,10,Fdiscrimination."
OL,12,FStuart Stevens, chief officer of the
OL,13,Fservice, said that no form of
OL,14,Fbullying, harassment or discrimination
OL,15,Fwould be tolerated "and action is
OL,16,Ftaken where issues are reported".
OL,18,FA confidential service has been
OL,19,Flaunched to allow concerns to be
OL,20,Freported anonymously, he added.
